        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size: 22px; line-height: 1.2; font-weight: 500">Bronte Capital Reviews Strategy After Losses </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">John Hempton’s Bronte Capital is <a href="https://www.hedgeweek.com/losses-prompt-bronte-capital-strategy-rethink/" target="_blank">rethinking</a> its investment strategy after posting its worst monthly returns in two years. The hedge fund reported a 5.6% loss in September due to mismatches in its long and short positions. Hempton has signaled that the firm will seek new ways to minimize risk as global equity markets continue to rise, squeezing short bets. The review comes as other hedge funds face similar challenges in a high-growth market, where traditional shorting strategies are becoming increasingly difficult to manage effectively.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
