        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size: 22px; line-height: 1.2; font-weight: 500">Brazilian Hedge Funds Score Big on Rate Bets</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">Brazilian hedge funds had a rare <a href="https://www.bnnbloomberg.ca/business/international/2024/10/15/bearish-rate-bets-hand-win-to-brazils-battered-hedge-funds/" target="_blank">win</a> in September, thanks to bets on higher local rates and lower yields abroad. Funds like Legacy Capital and Ace Capital posted their best returns of the year as Brazil's fiscal outlook fueled rising swap rates. Hedge funds are skeptical about the government's ability to stabilize public debt, which has led to increased pessimism on domestic assets. An index tracking Brazil's hedge funds rose 1.1% last month, outpacing the broader benchmark. Despite challenges, these funds are finding opportunities in the country’s uncertain fiscal environment.</p>
        </mj-text>
